Sentencas: SrFe0.9-xW0.1TixO3-$ (SFWT, x = 0.1 and 0.2) perovskite oxides are synthesized by combustion process.
Titulo: Investigation into structure and property of W and Ti co-doped SrFeO3 perovskite as electrode of symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The experimental and computational analyses are conducted to reveal the effect of dopant W and Ti on the material properties and structure.
Titulo: Investigation into structure and property of W and Ti co-doped SrFeO3 perovskite as electrode of symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The crystal structure transform from tetragonal (I4/m) to cubic(pm3m) when temperature is higher than 700 degrees C. Substitution of Fe with Ti can enhance the lattice structure.
Titulo: Investigation into structure and property of W and Ti co-doped SrFeO3 perovskite as electrode of symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: However, the Ti incorporation causes the increase in thermal expansion coefficient above 700 degrees C.
Titulo: Investigation into structure and property of W and Ti co-doped SrFeO3 perovskite as electrode of symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The XPS and TG analyses show that the Ti incorporation also decreases oxygen activity.
Titulo: Investigation into structure and property of W and Ti co-doped SrFeO3 perovskite as electrode of symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Thus, it is important to optimize the Ti content to design the SFWT materials to gain fast kinetics and high stability.
Titulo: Investigation into structure and property of W and Ti co-doped SrFeO3 perovskite as electrode of symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The total conductivity (48 S cm-1), polarization resistances of symmetric single cell (0.28 U cm2), and durability (150 h, at 750 degrees C) reveal that the SrFe0.8W0.1Ti0.1O3-$ is a promising electrode materials for symmetric fuel cell.
Titulo: Investigation into structure and property of W and Ti co-doped SrFeO3 perovskite as electrode of symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The first-principles calculation suggests that the Fe-O bond in SFWT dominates electric conductivity and can be suitably tailored by the dopant Ti and W. (c) 2022 Hydrogen Energy Publications LLC.
